    <div class='general-text-downloads'>
        <p>If you wish to play ERS, APS, or WMC, you <em><strong>MUST</strong></em> go to the options and choose 'Long' for your preferences - I will be copying the relevant items over to the other preferences in due course. If you do not use long preferences, none of the balancing will be present and you will experience a lack of balance amongst other issues!</p>
        <p>GT is not yet rebalanced properly. This will be coming in version 1.6 of the mod, therefore please consider GT non-playable with Redux. Apologies for the delay in getting this done, but I am only one person.</p>
        <p>The race lengths in Endurance are controlled via the race length preferences - short will give you 6 hour races, medium will give 12 hours, and long will give you a 24 hour race. It is up to you if you want to play every race as a specific length. One suggestion is to decide on a couple of marquee races for your season and have just one as a 24h, one as a 12h, and the rest as 6h. In the end, it is up to you.</p>
        <p>I will suggest just avoiding interviews entirely for now - they are slow, buggy and really are of little gameplay value.</p>
        <p>Please report all bugs to me as you find them, along with screenshots where possible (the message that pops up before the game force closes does not count, it offers no help to where the bug is). I have done my best to ensure the game will not force close on you by playing over 4 dozen seasons, but there still may be a couple of things that slipped through. The best place to report bugs is via <a target='_blank' href='https://discord.gg/PkSnphxPtj'>the Discord</a>, in the #rebirth-redux channel.</p>
        <p>To increase AI competitiveness, use the AI difficulty slider in the game options - this affects their part development by giving them bonuses (as much as I hate AI cheating, they really need to on this occasion). 20 is the maximum and after ERS *you will suffer*. If you find your progress too slow, drop the slider down. I recommend setting the slider to 10, then adjusting to your preferences.</p>
