        <h3 class='header'>My game is crashing on startup/starting a new save!</h3>
        <p>This can be from you trying to use other workshop mods with this mod, or having leftover files from any other large mod you may have already been using (such as FIRE Fantasy). You should disable every other mod you may have active, anything that tries to edit databases will conflict with Redux. If you have disabled all of your Workshop mods and still have issues, reinstall the game to ensure you have vanilla files, then follow the installation steps above. You can, however, use mods that replace models or add new livery layouts.</p>

        <h3 class='header'>I have white squares where logos should be!</h3>
        <p>This will be because you skipped a step, naughty naughty! Make sure you have the Rebirth: Logo Pack installed from the Steam Workshop, and activated, from steps 4 and 5 above.</p>

        <h3 class='header'>I cannot get the Rebirth: Logo Pack because I do not have the game on Steam!</h3>
        <p>Then I can guess you have a pirated version. While I have no personal issues with what you do, I will not support a pirated version of the game. There are two reasons for this - the first is that pirated games can cause unforeseen issues and I do not want to waste time I could spend having a cup of tea on chasing issues around that were caused by your pirated version (it has happened before). The second reason is that the Rebirth: Logo Pack is not mine, and thus I cannot offer a non-Steam version. This will never change, I know there are some regions that either cannot get the game, or it is prohibitively expensive, but this is the way it is. If it is cost related, Humble Bundle sometimes has it for cheap, and it regularly goes for very cheap on Steam.</p>
